                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12879121" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2010 21:13:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes the issue and cleans up a tiny bit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879125" author="stack" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2010 21:25:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks fine but what changed such that 2691 broke reinitialization of HRS?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12879130" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2010 21:41:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh actually it&apos;s broken but not the way I was thinking. So when a session is expired we do this in the region server;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (state == KeeperState.Expired) {
      LOG.error(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ZooKeeper session expired&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; restart =
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.conf.getBoolean(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hbase.regionserver.restart.on.zk.expire&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;);
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (restart) {
        restart();
      } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
        abort(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;ZooKeeper session expired&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But now we get the YouAreDeadException much sooner than the session expiration, which is good, but we don&apos;t do the restart check. Just adding it there will fix the issue. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879136" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2010 22:04:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we are removing the notion of RS restart anyway, I&apos;ll just clean that up from TestZK and commit my patch above. Objections?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12879142" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 15 Jun 2010 22:14:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed the patch with some more cleanup for RS restart (but not the code from HRS).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017634" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
